	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I wasn't aware of HMOS, but according to Wikipedia it's also known as "depletion-load NMOS".  The 2 6500 datasheets I just looked at (Rockwell and Commodore) both say it's "N-channel, silicon-gate, depletion-load technology".
<br />
<br />2A03 is a clone (excluding the patented BCD mode), I'd assume it's made on the same way..?  If that's true, maybe this is accurate enough:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.zimmers.net/anonftp/pub/cbm/documents/chipdata/r650x/r650x-15.gif">http://www.zimmers.net/anonftp/pub/cbm/ ... 50x-15.gif</a><!-- m -->

		

